 "LoaiTu": "noun", "PhienAm": "/\\u02ccst\\u00e6\\u0261\\u02c8fl\\u0435\\u026a\\u0283\\u0259n/"}, {"TuVung": "monetarism", "Nghia": "ch\\u00ednh s\\u00e1ch ti\\u1ec1n t\\u1ec7", "ViDuNguCanh": "The monetarist approach to economic policy emphasizes the role of monetary aggregates, such as the money supply, in determining economic activity.", "LoaiTu": "noun", "PhienAm": "/m\\u0259\\u02c8n\\u025bt\\u0259r\\u026az\\u0259m/"}, {"TuVung": "comparative advantage", "Nghia": "l\\u1ee3i th\\u1ebf so s\\u00e1nh", "ViDuNguCanh": "The theory of comparative advantage suggests that countries should specialize in producing goods for which they have a lower opportunity cost, and trade with other countries to meet their needs.", "LoaiTu": "phrase", "PhienAm": "/k\\u0259m\\u02c8p\\u00e6r\\u0259t\\u026av \\u0259d\\u02c8v\\u00e6nt\\u026ad\\u0292/"}]	2026-05-01 15:33:30.457274	f
